 weak dipolar interaction, irrespective of $A^{}_r$,\n$\\alpha$, and the field directions. Notably, the magnetic interaction enhances\n$E^{}_H$ if $A^{}_r$ is enormous and the magnetic field is along the long axis\nof the system. These results are beneficial in various applications of interest\nsuch as digital data storage, spintronics, etc.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Aug 2021 08:51:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-25"}
